In this work, the structure, density and mechanical properties of novel AlNbTiV high entropy alloy were examined. The alloy had single bcc phase coarse-grained structure and low density of 5.59 g cm À 3 after homogenization. The compressive yield strength of the alloy gradually decreased from 1020 MPa at room temperature to 685 MPa at 800 1C, and then dropped to 158 MPa at 1000 1C.
